    "body": "Totally, there should be an exception `@updateable parameters require at least one address for access restriction`\r\n\r\nI was also thinking perhaps a static-sized array should be allowed, e.g.\r\n```python\r\nowners: address[5]\r\n\r\n@updateable(owners)\r\ntransaction_limit: wei_value\r\n```\r\nwhich gives\r\n```python\r\ndef set_transaction_limit(_transaction_limit: wei_value):\r\n    assert msg.sender in owners\r\n    self.transaction_limit = _transaction_limit\r\n```\r\nAlthough I'm pretty sure the `item in fixed_array` syntax doesn't work yet for viper, even though it would be a static gas computation",
